,Recommended,225000,8497216,"Posted: 1 January, 2014",all,Dark Blue Monkey,"This may be the shortest of the Tomb Raider games.  It's set after Tomb Raider IV, when Lara's supposed to have died (I won't ruin the surprise, but there's a Tomb Raider VI after this one ;-)   It's chopped up into small stories, which break up the game into nice little episodes set at different times and in different locations.   The original Tomb Raiders can really drag sometimes, but this one has good pacing, an interesting story, and there's just enough variety to keep you interested.   It does have a few bugs, though, which can be a pain, but they're easily avoided if you keep a walkthrough handy.   As with all the original series TR's, level design and low poly models are really starting to show their age now, which is a shame, but it's a good member of the series, and a great trip down memory lane. Well Recommended for holiday fun."
