,Recommended,225000,35360647,Posted: 30 September,all,PookPunk,"Tomb Raider: Chronicles is linear and quite short. It took me roughly 5-6hrs. The level environments are small in scale compared to Tomb Raider 1-4 and feel more compact. Honestly, this made it harder to maneuver Lara through tight corridors, or perhaps the game responded awkwardly to my Xbox controller. However, my Xbox controller works fine with Tomb Raider 2-4 (the original game requires Xpadder).The game is presented decently, but there is no story in Chronicles. Instead, the game is divided into four sections that recount some of Lara’s past adventures.The first section are the Rome levels that provide throwbacks to the original Tomb Raider and some Tomb Raider 2 Venice vibes (without the speed boat). These levels focus on exploration and puzzles mostly.The second section is Russia and these levels pronounce all the action elements from the series. The Russia portion reminded me of the offshore rig and diving levels from Tomb Raider 2.The fourth section takes a younger Lara introduced at the beginning of Tomb Raider: The Last Revelation and strands her on a haunted Irish isle without weapons. These sections are very survival horror based with lots of puzzle solving. This portion of the game was my favorite as the levels were atmospheric and did something different for the series.The last section takes place in a high-tech skyscraper in New York City. These levels resembled the Area-51 levels from Tomb Raider 3 and focus more on stealth sequences. These levels are the most challenging in the game. Also, the last level “Red Alert” is very buggy. Certain bugs can prevent the player from finishing the level, so it’s a good idea to have multiple saves. And save frequently!While the Russia and VCI skyscraper sections are slight improvements from the contemporary levels from Tomb Raider 2 and 3, neither live up to the franchise name. Still, these levels are straight forward enough and presented better via the in-game cutscenes and Hollywood inspired approach. The game design in Chronicles is never intelligent like it was in The Last Revelation, nor does it ever feel as challenging like Tomb Raider 3.Overall, Tomb Raider Chronicles is rather average. The first section is too linear and easy. It’s a far cry to what Tomb Raider 1-4 are. The environments are dense and lack the scale as big of previous installments. For that reason alone, makes Chronicles a tad lackluster, but there are still a slew of entertaining gimmicks and challenges in Chronicles.PROS:+The Ireland levels remain the best section in the game+Decent presentationCONS:-Last level (Red Alert) very buggy-Rome levels are too linear and easy-Environments lack the scale of the previous games"
