,Not Recommended,225000,25694839,"Posted: 25 September, 2016",all,Mr. Blue Sky,"After the events of The Last Revelation, it seemed that Core wouldn't make any more Tomb Raider games until the PS2 was out. However, we all just couldn't get enough of Lara Croft and thus we got Chronicles which was blatantly thrown together and boy does it really show.In terms of gameplay, it's more or less the same as the previous games but admittedly, I really liked that they gave you the ability to roll out forwards through a crawlspace instead of having to turn around just to get down and that's literally the one good thing I can say about this game. There are many badly designed levels such as Russia where half of the time you are going through corridors in a submarine and then there's two minutes of exploring in the open water. The last level of the game is heavily bugged which the only way to counter them is to not save at all in certain parts because it will screw you over if you load up the game there.Story-wise. we are given four different adventures of Lara Croft through her years but the first part they bring back Larson and Pierre from the first game which doesn't make any sense at all. This even takes place before TR1 so they made a massive plothole just from that. According to the trailer, Lara infiltrates the Russian base in 1984 which is where she would be only 16. Yeah, not buying that. Her trip to Ireland takes place in 1979 with her backpack yet she doesn't actually get that until she went to Cambodia with Von Croy in 1984 so... yeah, continuity errors everywhere. That shows how badly thought out they were for the story.Would only recommend this game if you intend to play through all the Tomb Raider games. Otherwise, not really worth the time."
